%h1 FlippyWindow
.flippywindow
  %h2.flippywindow__blurb FlippyWindow is a simple Windows application that non-destructively flips any part of your screen horizontally, in realtime and using minimal resources.
  .flippywindow__screenshot
    %img{:src => %"https://www.robotinaponcho.net/flippywindow/screenshot.png"}
  %p.flippywindow__blurb.flippywindow__blurb--second Flipping images (or viewing things with a mirror) is a technique used to <a href="#">help view things with "fresh eyes"</a> which can aid with <a href="#">spotting visual issues</a>.
.download
  %h2.download__download
    %a.download__download__link{:href => "#"} Download<span> FlippyWindow</span> from <img class="download__download__link__image" src="itchio.svg">
  %ul.download__information-list
    %li.download__information-list__item
      %strong FlippyWindow requires Windows Vista or later.
    %li.download__information-list__item Nothing to install; just unzip and run the executable.
    %li.download__information-list__item FlippyWindow is <a href="https://www.robotinaponcho.net/git/?p=flippywindow.git">open-source</a> (and <a href="https://github.com/damiendart/flippywindow">on GitHub</a>).
